> approval we need. It is hard to argue with the Gods.
[...]
> Enforcement is a bit harder. I've been trying to find out how Sanom 
> handle it. Power seems to come in two forms - money and "physical"
> strength.
[...] 
> Delgath (our guide) was rather unclear on where the money for bounties
> comes from. Apparently there is some "City Treasury" which funds them,
> and which is in turn funded by sales of real-estate in the city, and
> similar things. We would have to see whether a similar account could
> be set up for us in our city, and how we could fill it.
[...]
> I would like to talk with the Wizards and Gods of the world before we
> do anything.

Note that none of the problems above apply in the other world being
considered for settlement by the Agoran community, the AgoraMOO.
There, power is only defined as 'physical' which currently reduces
to having programming or wizard permissions, and more than half of the
Agoran community is already installed on that world with that kind of
power, which means that the world effectively already belongs to
Agora. The 'gods' are ourselves.


